 Enyinnaya Abaribe, Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, Abia South. It is co-sponsored by Senators Yahaya Oloriegbe, APC, Kwara Central; Sabi Aliyu Abdullahi, Niger North; Chukwuka Utazi, Enugu North; Solomon Adeola, Lagos West and Sadiq Umar, Kwara North. Vanguard News Nigeria By Henry Umoru THE Senate Tuesday suspended all parliamentary activities, both at Plenary and at the levels of Committees. Prior to adjournment Tuesday, the Senate sat for just five minutes from 10:55 to 11:00 am as a result of the death of Senator Ignatius Longjan, All Progressives Congress, APC, Plateau… February 11, 2020 In "News" THE Senate, Tuesday adjourned plenary for lack of quorum, as only 10 Senators were present, and fixed the next legislative day for Wednesday, January 23. January 22, 2019 In "News" FOR the third time in two weeks, the Inspector General of Police, IGP, Ibrahim Idris who was billed to appear before the Senate today has shunned the Senators. May 9, 2018 In "News"